            <div class="text" style="margin-left: 60px;">

               <br/>
               <br/>

               <br/>
               <br/>

         <div id="MainContent_divDnData">
          <div align="left" style="margin-left: 20px; background-color: #F5F5F5; border: 1px solid #666666; padding: 5px;">
           <div align="right" class="displaydata2" style="padding-bottom: 2px;">

           <span class="tablehead2">
            Mathematics Advanced, BA (7114)
           </span>
           <span class="tabledata1">
            Required Credits: 120Program Version: FS13
           </span>
           <br>
            <br>
             <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
              Requirement 1: University Tier I Writing
              <br/>
             </div>
             <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
              University Tier I Writing: The required number of courses from 1 of the following sets of courses
             </div>
             <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 100px; text-indent: -20px;">
              WRA: 1. WRA: 1 course from WRA110, WRA115, WRA120, WRA125, WRA130, WRA135, WRA140, WRA145, WRA150, WRA195H, LB133, AL192, AL192H
             </div>
             <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 100px; text-indent: -20px;">
              James Madison Writing: 2. James Madison Writing: 2 courses from MC111, MC112
             </div>
             <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 100px; text-indent: -20px;">
              Residential College Writing: 3. Residential College Writing: 2 courses from RCAH111, RCAH112
             </div>
             <br>
              <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
               Requirement 2: University Mathematics
               <br/>
              </div>
              <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
               University Mathematics: The required number of courses from 1 of the following sets of courses
              </div>
              <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 100px; text-indent: -20px;">
               MTH2: 1 course
              </div>
              <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 140px; text-indent: -20px;">
               At least 1 course from LB118, MTH110, MTH116, MTHRQMT, MTHWAIV1, MTHWAIV2, Mathematics Pre-Matriculation, Mathematics Post-Matriculation
              </div>
              <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 100px; text-indent: -20px;">
               MTH1: 2 courses
              </div>
              <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 140px; text-indent: -20px;">
               At least 1 course from MTH103, MTH103WAIV
              </div>
              <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 140px; text-indent: -20px;">
               At least 1 course from MTH112, MTH114, MTH124, MTH132, MTH152H, MTH201, STT200, STT201
              </div>
              <br>
               <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                Requirement 3: University IAH201 - IAH210
                <br/>
               </div>
               <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                University IAH201 - IAH210: 4 credits from IAH201, IAH202, IAH203, IAH204, IAH205, IAH206, IAH207, IAH208, IAH209, IAH210, RCAH201, ANY IAH BELOW 211
               </div>
               <br>
                <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                 Requirement 4: University IAH211 or higher
                 <br/>
                </div>
                <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                 University IAH211 or higher: 4 credits from IAH211A, IAH211B, IAH211C, IAH211D, IAH221A, IAH221B, IAH221C, IAH231A, IAH231B, IAH231C, IAH241A, IAH241B, IAH241C, IAH241D, IAH241E, IAH241F, RCAH202, TRANSFER IAH, ANY IAH211 OR HIGHER, approved LB courses
                </div>
                <br>
                 <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                  Requirement 5: University ISS200 Series
                  <br/>
                 </div>
                 <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                  University ISS200 Series: 4 credits from ISS210, ISS215, ISS220, ISS225, ISS230, ISS235, MC201, TRANSFER ISS 200 LEVEL, ANY ISS 200 LEVEL
                 </div>
                 <br>
                  <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                   Requirement 6: University ISS300 Series
                   <br/>
                  </div>
                  <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                   University ISS300 Series: 4 credits from ISS305, ISS308, ISS310, ISS315, ISS318, ISS320, ISS325, ISS327, ISS328, ISS330A, ISS330B, ISS330C, ISS335, ISS336, MC202, ANY ISS 300 LEVEL, approved LB courses
                  </div>
                  <br>
                   <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                    Requirement 7: University ISB
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                   <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                    University ISB: 3 credits from ISB200, ISB201, ISB202, ISB204, TRANSFER ISB, ISB ALTERNATIVE TRACK, ANY 3 CREDIT ISB COURSE
                   </div>
                   <br>
                    <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                     Requirement 8: University ISP
                     <br/>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                     University ISP: 3 credits from ISP203A, ISP203B, ISP205, ISP207, ISP209, ISP213H, ISP215, ISP217, ISP220, ISP221, TRANSFER ISP, ISP ALTERNATIVE TRACK, ANY 3 CREDIT ISP COURSE
                    </div>
                    <br>
                     <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                      Requirement 9: University Laboratory Experience
                      <br/>
                     </div>
                     <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                      University Laboratory Experience: The required number of credits from 1 of the following sets of courses
                     </div>
                     <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 100px; text-indent: -20px;">
                      Univ Lab: 2 credits
                     </div>
                     <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 140px; text-indent: -20px;">
                      At least 2 credits from ISB201L, ISB208L, ISP203L, ISP205L, ISP207L, ISP209L, ISP217L, ANY 2 CREDIT ISB/ISP LAB, LAB EXPERIENCE ALTERNATIVE TRACK, TRANSFER LAB
                     </div>
                     <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 100px; text-indent: -20px;">
                      Alternative: 2 credits
                     </div>
                     <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 140px; text-indent: -20px;">
                      At least 1 credit from ISB201L, ISB208L, ISP203L, ISP205L, ISP207L, ISP209L, ISP217L, ANY 2 CREDIT ISB/ISP LAB, LAB EXPERIENCE ALTERNATIVE TRACK, TRANSFER LAB
                     </div>
                     <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 140px; text-indent: -20px;">
                      At least 1 credit from an Alternative Track Lab credit
                     </div>
                     <br>
                      <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                       Requirement 10: University Diversity Distribution
                       <br/>
                      </div>
                      <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                       University Diversity Distribution: A total 2 courses
                      </div>
                      <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 100px; text-indent: -20px;">
                       At least 1 course from NationalIAH or ISS courses emphasizing national diversity or both national diversity and international and multicultural diversity
                      </div>
                      <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 100px; text-indent: -20px;">
                       At least 1 course from InternationalIAH or ISS courses emphasizing international and multicultural diversity or both national diversity and international and multicultural diversity
                      </div>
                      <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 45px;">
                       Conditions:
                       <br/>
                      </div>
                      <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 80px; text-indent: -20px;">
                       University Diversity Distribution: No more than 1 course from IAH or ISS emphasizing both national diversity and international and multicultural diversity in Requirement(s) 10
                      </div>
                      <br>
                       <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                        Requirement 11: Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Outside the Department
                        <br/>
                       </div>
                       <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                        Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Outside the Department: 3 credits from biological science, entomology, microbiology, physiology, plant biology, or zoology.
                       </div>
                       <br>
                        <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                         Requirement 12: Major - Mathematics Advanced BA  - Chemistry
                         <br/>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                         Major - Mathematics Advanced BA  - Chemistry: 1 course from CEM141, CEM151, CEM181H, LB171
                        </div>
                        <br>
                         <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                          Requirement 13: Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Physics
                          <br/>
                         </div>
                         <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                          Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Physics: 1 course from PHY183, PHY193H, LB273
                         </div>
                         <br>
                          <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                           Requirement 14: Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Lab
                           <br/>
                          </div>
                          <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                           Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Lab: 2 credits from a laboratory course.
                          </div>
                          <br>
                           <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                            Requirement 15: Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Foreign Language or Professional Education
                            <br/>
                           </div>
                           <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                            Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Foreign Language or Professional Education: The required number of courses from 1 of the following sets of courses
                           </div>
                           <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 100px; text-indent: -20px;">
                            Professional Education: 1. Professional Education: 1 course from completion of the Professional Education Courses in the Department of Teacher Education and first -year competency in a foreign language.
                           </div>
                           <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 100px; text-indent: -20px;">
                            Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Foreign Language or Professional Education: 2. Foreign Language: 1 course from second-year competency in a foreign language.
                           </div>
                           <br>
                            <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                             Requirement 16: Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Calculus I
                             <br/>
                            </div>
                            <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                             Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Calculus I: 1 course from MTH132, MTH152H, LB118
                            </div>
                            <br>
                             <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                              Requirement 17: Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Calculus II
                              <br/>
                             </div>
                             <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                              Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Calculus II: 1 course from MTH133, MTH153H, LB119
                             </div>
                             <br>
                              <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                               Requirement 18: Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Advanced Calculus
                               <br/>
                              </div>
                              <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                               Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Advanced Calculus: 1 course from MTH234, MTH254H, LB220
                              </div>
                              <br>
                               <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                                Requirement 19: Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Mathematics Snapshots
                                <br/>
                               </div>
                               <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                                Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Mathematics Snapshots: 1 course from MTH291
                               </div>
                               <br>
                                <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                                 Requirement 20: Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Advanced Linear Algebra
                                 <br/>
                                </div>
                                <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                                 Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Advanced Linear Algebra: 1 course from MTH317H
                                </div>
                                <br>
                                 <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                                  Requirement 21: Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Introduction to Advanced Analysis
                                  <br/>
                                 </div>
                                 <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                                  Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Introduction to Advanced Analysis: 1 course from MTH327H
                                 </div>
                                 <br>
                                  <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                                   Requirement 22: Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Advanced Ordinary Differential Equations
                                   <br/>
                                  </div>
                                  <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                                   Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Advanced Ordinary Differential Equations: 1 course from MTH347H
                                  </div>
                                  <br>
                                   <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                                    Requirement 23: Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Honors Algebra I and II
                                    <br/>
                                   </div>
                                   <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                                    Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Honors Algebra I and II: 2 courses from MTH418H, MTH419H
                                   </div>
                                   <br>
                                    <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                                     Requirement 24: Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Honors Analysis I and II
                                     <br/>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                                     Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Honors Analysis I and II: 2 courses from MTH428H, MTH429H
                                    </div>
                                    <br>
                                     <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                                      Requirement 25: Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Capstone in Mathematics
                                      <br/>
                                     </div>
                                     <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                                      Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Capstone in Mathematics: 1 course from MTH496
                                     </div>
                                     <br>
                                      <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                                       Requirement 26: Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Approved Courses
                                       <br/>
                                      </div>
                                      <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                                       Major - Mathematics Advanced BA - Approved Courses: 12 credits from approved courses with substantive high-level quantitative material at the 400-level or above.
                                      </div>
                                      <br>
                                       <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                                        Requirement 27: College Distribution
                                        <br/>
                                       </div>
                                       <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                                        College Distribution: 30 credits from courses numbered at the 300 and 400 levels. See academic advisor.
                                       </div>
                                       <br>
                                        <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                                         Requirement 28: Electives
                                         <br/>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                                         Electives: 0 credits from Electives at Michigan State University and transfer coursework.  This number can change based on the credits of the coursework taken to fulfill University, College, and Major requirements.  Please contact your academic advisor with any questions.
                                        </div>
                                        <br>
                                         <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                                          Requirement 29: University Residency
                                          <br/>
                                         </div>
                                         <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                                          University Residency: 30 credits from MSU coursework, 27 credits from MSU courses taken after reaching junior standing, 20 credits from courses offered by MSU while admitted to major &amp; 20 of the last 30 credits must be MSU courses.  Please see academic advisor.
                                         </div>
                                        </br>
